Hello there! If you've received a confirmation email, then your application has been submitted successfully. It will be processed when we are able to view grades - probably early June. 

Yep, that's totally fine.

Hi! I just submitted a major form to declare early for the CS major. Are there certain next steps I should take, or do I now wait until the results, (after receiving the automated confirmation email)? Also, is there a way we can have a copy of our application?

For courses that I skipped with AP Credit, it didn't allow me to just put "AP Credit" and leave the other areas blank, so I just put AP Credit and the first semester I was here, and left the grade field and instructor blank. Is that ok?

Thank You :)
